---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Dashboard" section="dashboard" description="Clerri Marketing Strategy Hub — personal working document for Jerris Heaton, Senior Director of Marketing">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">↓ Working strategy hub — v3 · Sub-page tracker</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Take the practice <em>back.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">A functional, sharable strategy hub for Clerri's marketing function — Strategic priorities, verified competitive intelligence, ad spend tiers, ICP/ABM targets, and a working 90-day plan. Personal tracking auto-saves locally. Export to markdown to share with the team.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <!-- Key stats -->
  <div class="grid-4">
    <div class="metric-card"><div class="v">5,000+</div><div class="l">practices on platform</div></div>
    <div class="metric-card"><div class="v">7 / 10</div><div class="l">top US DSOs</div></div>
    <div class="metric-card"><div class="v">72M+</div><div class="l">uninsured US adults</div></div>
    <div class="metric-card"><div class="v">$17B+</div><div class="l">AUM at Charlesbank</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- Top findings -->
  <h2>The three findings that <em>change the plan.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:60ch">From 4 parallel deep-research workstreams: competitor intel, SEM landscape, AI stack, partnerships. Verified data layered onto Jim's stated priorities.</p>

  <div class="grid-3">
    <div class="callout">
      <div class="lbl">Finding 01 · Competitive</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.25rem 0 0.5rem;color:var(--zest)">BoomCloud's "Patient Marketplace" is a paper tiger.</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">ThePatientMarketplace.com gets <strong>2,400 visits/month with 79.6% bounce rate</strong>. WordPress directory propped up by paid display ads. Clerri's 5,000+ practice density + modest investment dwarfs them within 6 months.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="callout zest-hi">
      <div class="lbl">Finding 02 · Insider Threat</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.25rem 0 0.5rem">Subscribili is underestimated — ex-Membersy CEO.</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem">CEO Sudha Vetri is a <strong>Membersy alumna</strong>. $4.3M seed from Vyne Dental + Darby Group (strategics). Acquired Stream Dental April 2025. DMPO + TPA licensed. Structurally more dangerous than Plan Forward.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="callout mint">
      <div class="lbl">Finding 03 · Macro</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.25rem 0 0.5rem">Anti-PPO sentiment at peak intensity.</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem"><strong>30% of dentists dropped insurance networks Q4 2024</strong> (ADA HPI). FFS practices grew 6% → 16%. Typical dentist writes off $3-6M lifetime to PPOs. "Escape PPO write-offs" is the lead message.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Quick start -->
  <h2>Quick start — <em>your first 14 days.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft)">Check these off as you complete them. Auto-saved to your browser. Export to markdown anytime via the sidebar.</p>

  <div data-section="quickstart">
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-01-cto-1on1" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Schedule recurring 1:1 with the CEO — weekly first 90 days, monthly after</div>
        <div class="task-meta">Per the operating cadence — Jim is the only marketing stakeholder above you</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-02-team-intros" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Meet with every existing marketing team member individually</div>
        <div class="task-meta">3 marketers — understand current ownership, strengths, gaps before assigning anything</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-03-sales-cs-product" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Cross-functional intros: Sales leadership, CS (John), Product (Jacob)</div>
        <div class="task-meta">Establish marketing's relationship with each function — bi-weekly cadence going forward</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-04-martech-audit" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Martech audit — Pardot, Salesforce, attribution, analytics, integrations</div>
        <div class="task-meta">What's wired vs. unwired? What's the data quality bottleneck?</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-05-pardot-otterly" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Sign up for Otterly.ai ($29/mo) — start AEO baseline immediately</div>
        <div class="task-meta">top strategic concern. Document current state across ChatGPT/Perplexity/Claude/Gemini before any changes</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-06-customer-calls" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Schedule 5-10 customer interviews across segments (solo / group / DSO)</div>
        <div class="task-meta">First 30 days. Real conversations, not survey forms</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-07-competitor-teardown" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Personally teardown BoomCloud's ThePatientMarketplace.com</div>
        <div class="task-meta">Validate the "paper tiger" finding. Document what works, what's broken, what Clerri does differently</div>
      </div>
    </label>
    <label class="task">
      <input type="checkbox" data-track="qs-08-quick-win-email" data-section="quickstart" />
      <div class="task-content">
        <div class="task-title">Week-1 quick win: ship the markdown → branded HTML email workflow</div>
        <div class="task-meta">Already proven at CareCloud, 90% time savings. The strategic priority is visible AI impact — this is the "I'm here to deliver" moment</div>
      </div>
    </label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block" style="margin-top:1rem">
    <div class="note-label">Personal notes — first 14 days <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="quickstart-notes" placeholder="Observations, blockers, who said what, things that surprised you..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <!-- Section directory -->
  <h2>Strategy sections</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft)">Each topic has its own sub-page with checklist tasks, evaluation notes, and status tracking. Click a section to dive in.</p>

  <div class="grid-3" style="margin-top:1rem">
    <a href="/clerri/foundation" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">01 · STRATEGIC</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Foundation</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Strategic priorities, revenue model, audience map. Three-bucket revenue framing.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/market" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">02 · CONTEXT</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Market</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">PPO compression, DSO landscape, 30% dropped networks Q4 2024, FFS migration.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/competitors" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">03 · INTEL</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Competitors</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">5 competitors with verified pricing, funding, headcount, monthly ad spend estimates.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/ad-spend" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">04 · BUDGET</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Ad Spend Tiers</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Light / Moderate / Aggressive / Market-Leader spend allocations with channel breakdown.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/icp" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">05 · ABM</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">ICP & ABM Targets</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Top-30 DSO target list with decision-makers, approach vectors, displacement status.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/ad-strategy" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">06 · CREATIVE</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Ad Creative & Targeting</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Persona-specific messaging hooks, formats, targeting layers, what works vs avoid.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/aeo-seo" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">07 · DISCOVERY</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">AEO / SEO / SEM</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Keyword universe with volume/CPC. Kleer/Membersy = defensive, not conquest.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/directory" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">08 · CONSUMER</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Patient Directory</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">The single highest-ROI competitive move. Phased rollout to neutralize BoomCloud.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/ai-stack" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">09 · TOOLING</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">AI Marketing Stack</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Day-1 stack: 6 tools, $400-900/mo. Replaces $5-15K of enterprise tooling.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/workflows" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">10 · BUILD</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Workflow Recipes</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">8 concrete workflows with platform stacks, build effort, costs per workflow.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/website" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">11 · BRAND</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Website & Messaging</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">"Take your practice back" framework. Site architecture + conversion path.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/channels" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">12 · MIX</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Channel Strategy</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Foundational / Performance / Strategic / Experimental tiers with allocation.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/partners" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">13 · BD</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Partnership Targets</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Top 5 first-90-day partners: Sunbit, HSO API Exchange, Dental Intelligence, DEO, Glenn Vo.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/conferences" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">14 · EVENTS</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Conferences 2026</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">ADSO Summit (Jun), DEO Intensive, ADA SmileCon (final year!), GNYDM.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/team" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">15 · ORG</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Team & Operations</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Hire sequence, agency strategy, cadence.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/horizontal" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">16 · FUTURE</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Horizontal Expansion</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Hint Health (DPC) reference architecture. Vision membership = white space.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/90day" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">17 · PLAN</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">First 90 Days</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Diagnose / Plan+Quick Wins / Execute+Build phases with task tracking.</p>
    </a>
    <a href="/clerri/metrics" class="card" style="text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
      <div class="mono" style="font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--clerri-green);letter-spacing:0.15em">18 · MEASURE</div>
      <h3 style="margin:0.5rem 0 0.25rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Metrics & Questions</h3>
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Leading/lagging indicators, two-bucket ROI, 12 things to validate during onboarding.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <div class="callout zest-hi" style="margin-top:3rem">
    <div class="lbl">How this hub works</div>
    <p><strong>Checkboxes, notes, and statuses auto-save</strong> to your browser. Nothing is sent to a server. Use the sidebar's "Export markdown" button to share progress with the team. "Reset state" wipes all tracking if you want to start fresh.</p>
  </div>

</div>

</ClerriLayout>
